<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-10-31T15:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-10-31T15:00:00-05:00" n="676" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d676">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 861.00/3037</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to the Ambassador in Russia</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_FDR1" type="to"><hi rend="italic">Francis</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-10-31T15:00:00-05:00"><hi rend="italic">October
                                            31, 1918, 3 p.m.</hi></date></dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>331. Your 510, October 23, 6 p.m., under consideration. For your
                                confidential information: command of forces in northern Russia was
                                assigned to the British by decision of War Council at Versailles.
                                Any change would require consideration by the Council. War
                                Department would probably agree to control of American troops by
                                Russian only if officer selected were of definitely approved
                                capacity.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed><persName corresp="#p_LR1"><hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi></persName></signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>